name:
Photon 1.25 
(c) 2024 ermouth 

Run attachment `index.html` to start Photon. 

See https://github.com/ermouth/couch-photon 
repo for more details.
versions:
## 1.25.4

[Restore…] options are adapted for JSON sources, 
`Skip deleted` option now works ok for JSON 
dumps.

Fixed saving docs with `_deleted:true` added 
manually in doc editor.

Fixed intermittent Undo and in-place code issues 
in doc editor.

## 1.25.3

Fixed several issues with doc editor when editing 
a deleted doc.

Compatibility with Chrome49 for XP again restored.

## 1.25.2

[Restore…] dialog now accepts .json files containing 
an array of raw docs, with or without revisions. Each 
doc in array still must have an `_id`.

## 1.24.35

Purge now works fine with deleted docs selected 
in `_changes` feed UI.

Purge also received new All revs mode, which tries 
to get all strored revs of each doc and then to 
purge them all.

Fix: purge no more fails when deleting more than 
`purge/max_revisions_number` of docs at a time.

## 1.24.32

Added `smoosh.ignore` config section description. 

[Unzip…] button renamed into [Restore…]. Restore 
dialog now accepts not only ZIPs but also JSON 
file dumps saved from `_changes` or `_all_docs` 
endpoints. JSON must contain all data, so 
`?include_docs=true&attachments=true` request 
URL parts are vital.

## 1.24.30

Tab titles received icons. Code editor dark theme 
colors are bit powdered.

## 1.24.26

JSON serialization improvements: long key ladders 
of deeply-nested values (ie deep Mango queries) are 
now flattened.

New experimental feature: click on type indicator 
in raw JSON editors converts JSON syntax to JS – 
functions are unwrapped, keys are more concise. 
May be useful for design docs.

## 1.24.25

Better attribute coloring in HTML editors. 

View column `/dt` modifier now understands timestamps 
in base36.

Prettier JSON serialization: small objects and arrays 
are shown as single lines. 

Tested for CouchDB 3.3.3, `_config` popup help updated 
to support newly introduced config keys.

## 1.24.24

Doc id generator in [Clone…] dialog now tries to infer 
source id structure and generate similarly looking 
random `_id`. Couch `/_uuid` API endpoint is still 
used for uuid-like structures.

## 1.24.22

Cloning a doc no more immediately saves the clone,
new doc opens in editor first.

New never saved docs denote themselves as changed 
(blue dot) in tab bar.

## 1.24.21

More emoji-related small fixes here and there. 
Added clarification of empty `.settings.roles` into 
readme.

## 1.24.20

Fixed open/close chevrons misplacement in Firefox. 
Emoji related minor UI fixes for Diff and File editor 
components. 

## 1.24.19

SQL to Mango converter now prepends `(*UTF8)` prefix to 
RegExp-like queries, which provides utf8-aware search 
for `ILIKE` and RegExps with `(?i)` prefix.

Added venerable FiraCode to Code font selector at the 
`About` tab. FiraCode font isn’t shipped with Photon, 
you need to install it yourself.

## 1.24.17

Fixed sharding settings misbehavior in the [New DB…] dlg.

## 1.24.16

No more random cursor jumps in View index in-place code 
editor. Emoji related minor UI fixes. 

## 1.24.15

JSON editor fix: Links to attachments with emojis in 
docname or filename no more point to 404. 

## 1.24.14

Local docs list now has `Include docs` switch. Grid 
view for `_local_docs` turns `include_docs` on, like
for `_all_docs`.

## 1.24.12

Large diffs are now multiline. Start screen logo 
is fixed. SQL `BETWEEN` no more casts number-like
strings to nums.

## 1.24.11

SQL queries now support `LIKE`, `ILIKE`,`BETWEEN`
and`NOT BETWEEN`.

## 1.24.10

SQL queries received MySQL-style RegExp syntax: 
`WHERE _id RLIKE '^ab?c'`. `REGEXP` and `RLIKE` are 
converted to Mango `{$regex:''}` conditional.

## 1.24.9

Fixed intermittent `Nothing found` text atop of search
results. Formatting for cells with `/int` modifier 
doesn’t crumble if preceding columns are joined.

Compatibility with Chrome49 restored, WinXP forever)

## 1.24.8

Fixed: issues with line numbers in JS view editor; 
malformed tooltips here and there; issues with selecting 
docs having emoji in `_id`; issues with searching emoji.

## 1.24.6

Mostly fixed inverted lightness of emojis in dark mode.
Startkey icon changed from funnel to more relevant key.

## 1.24.4

Mango and SQL queries which failed due to missing 
index now show `Create index` button after the error.
The button knows context and creates index to fullfill 
the query.

Old fashioned UI fold/unfold triangle arrows replaced 
with chevrons.

Fixed SQL/Mango qry editor buttons overlay for narrow 
screens.

## 1.24.2

Added interactive SQL queries feature, which 
translates SQL subset to Mango and queries 
current DB. Available in a dropdown where all 
views and queries live. Any named SQL query is 
stashed in localStorage and survives Photon reload,
like named Mango queries.

Grid/list switch behavior for bucket view fixed.

## 1.23

Deleted docs can be now edited and saved back.

Added `/curr` and `/int` modifiers to grid view. A
qry like `.price /curr` makes its column of values 
aligned right, fixpoint and monospaced.

Click on doc [Root▼] in JSON editor fold/unfolds all 
first-level doc subtrees. Also works in `_config`.

Added `_node/_local/_versions` support for Couch 3.3+,
exposed in `About` tab (`Node tools` section).

Added Photon history popup into `About` tab.

## 1.22

Added `Download doc as ZIP` button into doc editor.
Downloader puts the doc json and all doc attachments 
into zip as separate files.

The `Clear local settings` item of Logout menu now
opens dlg which allows to choose local settings to
wipe out.

Added stats into text attachments editor. Added 
`../` level up button into doc editor.

Max obj/array size to unfold in JSON ed is now 500.

Minor UI fixes.

## 1.21

New feature: DB conflicts list for CouchDB 2.3+.

New `Add view…` button in the DB docs/view panel.

`Alt+W` (or `Ctrl+W` on Mac) now closes current Photon 
internal tab.

Default view mode is now Grid

Link to logs for Couch 1.x is moved to About tab. 

Grid selectors like `.value.*.somefield /list` now work not 
only if `.value` is an array, but with objects as well. Very 
handy for reducers which return objects.

User info popup now has Forget viewstates command. The cmd
clears local state caches.

Photon is no more mirrored to AWS S3 CDN.

## 1.20

New major feature: dark theme. Settings are in `About` tab.

Minor UI tweaks and ZIP undump fixes.

## 1.19

Some refactoring, moving from ES5 to ES6.

New feature: expandable DB auto-groups. Grouping makes Photon
comfortable for nodes with thousands DBs. Tunable in settings.

Added response size/duration indicator at the bottom of 
view results. 

Photon default repo URL was changed, updates are now delivered 
strictly over https.

## 1.18

Mostly UI fixes and performance improvements. Starred DBs show
security and size regardless of Photon config.

## 1.17

Added Mango syntax validator into query editor. Added
Ping session config option. 

CouchDB 3.2 related: incompatible CSP config handling.

Added `Ctrl+S` and `Ctrl+Z` (`Cmd+S` and `Cmd+Z` for Mac) global 
keyboard shortcuts for config, doc and attachment editors.

Compatibility with old IEs is no more maintained.

## 1.16

Added Undo history panel into doc and config editors. The panel 
is a list of all json changes, and in most cases allows to 
undo json tree changes out of order.

## 1.15

Added left panel / top bar switch to match wide monitors better. 
Vertical panel only available for 1420px+ wide screens.

Max 15 tabs message removed, older tabs are auto-closed if needed.

Bucket stats numbers in DB list are clickable and show DB info.

Added typecast ` /cast` modifiers for selectors in grid view.

Added `Clone…` button in doc editor; basically `Save as…`.

Added `../` button in views, which opens bucket root doc list.

## 1.14

Added grid (table) representation mode for docs lists, view and 
Mango queries. Tables are copy/pastable to Excel. 

Added Include docs option for `/_all_docs` view, it is turned on 
automatically for grid view mode.

Views now memoize their particular source code editor state, as 
well as reduce level and grid settings.

## 1.12

Added ZIP dump/restore. A [Delete DB] dlg now offers to re-create 
DB(s) after deletion. Several JSON editor fixes and improvements. 
Task list grouping improved. 

TT Mono font excluded from the Photon package. 

## 1.11

Added `/_changes` feed view, added compound index stats for 
ddocs view.

## 1.10

Added index stats for each ddoc in ddocs view; also a lot of 
slight UI improvements.

## 1.9

Added: group DB sync; Couch perf test; CouchDB v3 support. 

## 1.8

Improved JSON editor, added `/_stats` graphs.

## 1.7

Added structured diff for doc revisions.

## 1.6

New features: editor for text-based attachments and doc purge. 
DB view received `db/_design_docs` and `db/_local_docs` modes.

## 1.4

Added access restrictions, Photon no more starts without 
authorization.

## 1.2

Added in-place editors for Erlang, JS and Mango view syntax.

## 0.9.99

More or less usable version with all basic features. March, 2018.
